Tp(t)=p(t+1)
Tp(t) =\int_0^tp(s)ds
Tp(t)=\int_0^1p(s)ds =\sum_{k=0}^na_k\frac{t^{k+1}}{k+1}
\implies
||T(p)||=\sum|\frac{a_k}{k+1}| \le1. \sum |a_k|=||p||
||T||=1
||p(t+1)||= \sum_{k=1}^{n}\binom{n}{n-1}a_n+\sum_{k=2}^{n}\binom{n}{n-2}......+\sum_{k=n}^{n}\binom{n}{0}
\lVert X^n\rVert=1
T(X^n)=\sum_{j=0}^n\binom njX^j
\lVert T(X^n)\rVert=\sum_{j=0}^n\binom nj=2^n
